               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$c - Type of number</strong> <div class="description">Type of patent document identifier</div>
         <div class="description2">
            <div class="description">Identifier is usually a number. Subfield $c may contain a term or a code
                                 identifying the type. The source of the code is <em>Standard Code for
                                       Identification of Different Kinds of Patent Documents</em> (WIPO ST.16) that is
                                 maintained by the World Intellectual Property Organization. The code is a one- or
                                 two-character code. Plain language terms are recorded as they appear on the item.
                                 Field 013 is repeated if there is more than one number to be recorded for an
                              item.
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
